#ROOM
Vnum     15000
Name     &GBase of the Great Elevators&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     You stand on the golden, rolling plains of Mulgore. Towering hundreds
of feet above you is the awe-inspiring Central Mesa of Thunder Bluff.
A massive wooden platform, operated by immense ropes and counterweights,
waits to carry travelers to the city above.
~
Exit
Direction up~
ToRoom    15001
Desc      You step onto the massive wooden elevator platform.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 15009 2 15000
  Reset E 1 15001 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15001
Name     &OInside the Great Elevator&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The massive wooden platform creaks and sways slightly as it ascends the
sheer rock face of the mesa. The view of Mulgore expanding below you is
breathtaking. The wind whips fiercely as you approach the peak.
~
Exit
Direction up~
ToRoom    15002
Desc      The elevator locks into place at the top of the mesa.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction down~
ToRoom    15000
Desc      The elevator descends back to the plains of Mulgore.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15002
Name     &GTop of the Elevators&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You step off the elevator and onto the lush, green grass of Thunder Bluff's
Central Mesa. The air here is thin, crisp, and smells of sweetgrass and
woodsmoke. To the north, a towering totem pole marks the center of the
city's main square.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    15003
Desc      The bustling Totem Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction down~
ToRoom    15001
Desc      The Great Elevator awaits.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 15009 2 15002
  Reset E 1 15001 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15003
Name     &GTotem Square&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     This is the heart of the Central Mesa. A massive, masterfully carved
totem pole towers into the sky, representing the unity of the Tauren
tribes. Tauren, Orcs, and Trolls mingle peacefully here. Pathways
branch out in all directions.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    15006
Desc      The northern path across the grass.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    15008
Desc      The path winds toward the Auction House.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    15002
Desc      The top of the Great Elevators.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    15014
Desc      The path winds toward the Wind Rider Roost.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset O 0 15000 1 15003
Reset M 0 15000 2 15003
  Reset E 1 15001 10 16
Reset M 0 15007 2 15003
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15004
Name     &GThunder Bluff Bank&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This large, open-air tent is constructed of thick kodo hides stretched
over heavy timber. It serves as the bank for the city. Despite the
lack of stone walls, the wealth of the Horde is well protected here by
several very large, very well-armed guards.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    15006
Desc      The northern walk of the Central Mesa.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction down~
ToRoom    15005
Desc      A ramp leads down into a secure earthen cellar.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 15005 1 15004
  Reset E 1 15001 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15005
Name     &dThunder Bluff Bank Vault&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    dark indoors~
Desc     Carved directly into the earth of the mesa, this cool, dry cellar holds
the heavy iron strongboxes that contain the city's reserves of gold and
valuable resources. 
~
Exit
Direction up~
ToRoom    15004
Desc      The main banking tent.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset O 0 15009 3 15005
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15006
Name     &GCentral Mesa - North Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The soft grass of the mesa is worn down into a distinct path here.
To the west is the large hide tent of the Thunder Bluff Bank, and to
the north, a rope bridge stretches precariously across the open sky
toward Spirit Rise.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    15018
Desc      The rope bridge to Spirit Rise.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    15003
Desc      Totem Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    15004
Desc      The Thunder Bluff Bank.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 15008 1 15006
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15007
Name     &GThunder Bluff Auction House&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This large tent is surprisingly noisy compared to the rest of the city.
Merchants and adventurers from across Kalimdor gather here to trade
goods. A raised wooden platform holds the auctioneers, who bark out
bids over the low rumble of the crowd.
~
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    15008
Desc      The eastern walk of the Central Mesa.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 15003 1 15007
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15008
Name     &GCentral Mesa - East Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The wind blows gently across the eastern side of the mesa. To the east
sits the busy Auction House tent, and further east, a massive rope
bridge connects to Elder Rise. To the south, the smell of roasted
meat drifts from the local inn.
~
Exit
Direction east~
ToRoom    15007
Desc      The entrance to the Auction House.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    15011
Desc      The path continues toward the Inn.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction west~
ToRoom    15003
Desc      Totem Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15009
Name     &GBloodhoof Village Inn - Entrance&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The largest tent on the Central Mesa, the inn is a welcoming haven
for all travelers. The floor is covered in soft, woven rugs, and the
air is warm and inviting. 
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    15011
Desc      The path leading back to the mesa proper.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
ToRoom    15010
Desc      The central hearth of the inn.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15010
Name     &GBloodhoof Village Inn - Hearth&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A large, circular fire pit dominates the center of the room. A massive
iron spit slowly turns a roasting plainstrider. Tauren sit on colorful
cushions, sharing stories, drinking water from hollowed horns, and
smoking ceremonial pipes.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    15009
Desc      The entrance to the inn.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 15004 1 15010
  Reset E 1 15005 10 17
Reset O 0 15003 2 15010
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     15011
Name     &GCentral Mesa - South Walk&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The path winds along the southern edge of the Central Mesa. To the
south is the entrance to the Bloodhoof Village Inn. To the west,
a prominent tent flanked by massive totems marks the dwelling of the
High Chieftain.
~
Exit
Direction north~
ToRoom    15008
Desc      The eastern walk of the mesa.
~
#ENDEXIT
Exit
Direction south~
